500
00:37:32,294 --> 00:37:34,237
I saw her many years ago.

501
00:37:35,408 --> 00:37:36,808
She was a child.

502
00:37:39,215 --> 00:37:41,365
Her parents had just been killed.

503
00:37:43,442 --> 00:37:44,763
She was crying.

504
00:37:45,939 --> 00:37:46,939
But she...

505
00:37:48,848 --> 00:37:50,117
She was brave.

506
00:37:57,153 --> 00:37:59,525
She crossed my mind...

507
00:38:02,054 --> 00:38:03,054
somehow.

508
00:38:04,424 --> 00:38:05,824
She never left it.

509
00:38:11,908 --> 00:38:13,033
I think...

510
00:38:15,512 --> 00:38:17,112
it's what they call...

511
00:38:19,050 --> 00:38:20,050
feelings.

512
00:38:22,175 --> 00:38:23,630
I think...

513
00:38:26,208 --> 00:38:27,615
I love her.

514
00:38:37,272 --> 00:38:39,225
Will she be safe now?

515
00:38:44,935 --> 00:38:46,035
You made her

516
00:38:47,714 --> 00:38:48,841
important.

517
00:39:02,940 --> 00:39:06,757
She is responsible
for the death of one of us.

518
00:39:18,726 --> 00:39:19,926
So who was he?

519
00:39:20,125 --> 00:39:22,526
How am I supposed
to make sense of any of this?

520
00:39:23,789 --> 00:39:25,320
Him, the plane,

521
00:39:25,922 --> 00:39:27,722
the guy who came after us.

522
00:39:28,343 --> 00:39:30,193
Did he say anything to you?

523
00:39:30,931 --> 00:39:32,381
Anything? Did he...

524
00:39:32,654 --> 00:39:34,454
tell you why he saved you?

525
00:39:39,893 --> 00:39:42,093
He asked me to give you something.

526
00:39:43,873 --> 00:39:45,023
The bald man.

527
00:39:51,003 --> 00:39:53,003
In the event that he couldn't.

528
00:40:08,164 --> 00:40:09,164
My dad...

529
00:40:09,910 --> 00:40:12,110
won this for me playing skee-ball.

530
00:40:13,405 --> 00:40:17,205
I was holding on to it in the backseat
when the bridge collapsed.

531
00:40:21,851 --> 00:40:23,701
I think you'll be safe now.

532
00:40:33,133 --> 00:40:36,583
When did you see the Observer?
And why didn't you tell me?

533
00:40:38,384 --> 00:40:39,734
What do you mean?

534
00:40:42,501 --> 00:40:45,150
- I just did tell you.
- No, that's not good enough.

535
00:40:45,318 --> 00:40:47,809
We are so close. I can't
let these guys get away again.

536
00:40:47,934 --> 00:40:50,116
They have the answers.
I know they do.

537
00:40:50,241 --> 00:40:51,591
Don't worry, son.

538
00:40:52,839 --> 00:40:54,489
You'll get your answer.

539
00:40:59,885 --> 00:41:02,834
Why don't we go for
a long drive together?

540
00:41:03,803 --> 00:41:07,255
Perhaps to pick up
a Tutti Frutti milkshake.

541
00:41:09,510 --> 00:41:12,010
The man you shot
was named Donald Long.

542
00:41:12,499 --> 00:41:15,945
Ballistics tied his gun to six unsolved
homicides up and down the East Coast.

543
00:41:16,070 --> 00:41:17,932
The earliest one
dates back ten years.

544
00:41:18,057 --> 00:41:19,757
- An assassin.
- Maybe.

545
00:41:20,009 --> 00:41:22,907
- Do we know who hired him this time?
- We don't know.

546
00:41:23,032 --> 00:41:25,625
Nothing in his car or on his person
gave any indication.

547
00:41:25,750 --> 00:41:27,750
What about the Observer's gun?

548
00:41:27,875 --> 00:41:31,105
Our techs had never seen anything like
it. They can't seem to make it fire.

549
00:41:31,230 --> 00:41:34,074
The best we can figure,
Peter shot off the last round.

550
00:41:35,363 --> 00:41:37,013
There's one more thing.

551
00:41:37,307 --> 00:41:40,462
The tip-off that the Observer
was spotted at that motel,

552
00:41:40,847 --> 00:41:43,166
it was called in from
one of the motel phones.

553
00:41:45,196 --> 00:41:47,896
What if he was trying
to protect Christine?

554
00:41:48,536 --> 00:41:52,134
And if he realized
he couldn't do it on his own?

555
00:41:52,730 --> 00:41:54,330
That's what I thought.

556
00:41:58,886 --> 00:42:02,636
If it's okay with you, I'd like
to take the rest of the day off.

557
00:42:04,981 --> 00:42:05,981
Sure.

558
00:42:07,005 --> 00:42:08,005
Big plans?

559
00:42:11,666 --> 00:42:13,153
Don't worry, Aunt Liv.

560
00:42:13,278 --> 00:42:15,257
I'll hold your hand.

561
00:42:16,259 --> 00:42:17,409
You'd better.

562
00:42:20,733 --> 00:42:22,033
I'm not gonna...

563
00:42:45,692 --> 00:42:47,292
Look how happy she is.

564
00:42:48,800 --> 00:42:52,000
It's a shame things
are about to get so hard for her.

